Calculate the absolute probability of an index case to case interval belonging to a transmission route component

Source: R/get_abs_prob.R
get_abs_prob.Rd

Calculate the absolute probability of an index case to case interval belonging to a transmission route component

Usage

get_abs_prob(dat, sigma = sd(dat), mu = mean(dat))

Arguments

dat

a (numeric) vector of index case to case intervals

sigma

standard deviation of underlying probability distribution; defaults to sd(dat)

mu

mean of underlying probability distribution; defaults to mean(dat)

Value

matrix where each row represents a transmission route and each column represents the absolue probability of belonging to that transmission route for each index case to case interval in dat

Examples

my_data<-c(rep(1,38),rep(2,39),rep(3,30),rep(4,17),rep(5,7))
get_abs_prob(my_data)
